cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper is primarily focused on robot learning for human-robot interaction, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves learning from human activity videos, which requires computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The proposed generative model for weakly supervised learning involves machine learning and probabilistic modeling (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the goal of the research is to improve the interaction between humans and robots, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
